Parker Solar Probe, FIELDS Radio Frequency Spectrometer, RFS, Low Frequency Receiver, LFR, Spectra, Level 2 (L2), 7 s and 56 s Data

(2020). Parker Solar Probe, FIELDS Radio Frequency Spectrometer, RFS, Low Frequency Receiver, LFR, Spectra, Level 2 (L2), 7 s and 56 s Data [Data set]. NASA Space Physics Data Facility. https://doi.org/10.48322/re4h-tk40 (CiteAs link). Accessed on .

ResourceID
spase://NASA/NumericalData/ParkerSolarProbe/FIELDS/RFS/Level2/LFR/PT7S

Description

PSP FIELDS Radio Frequency Spectrometer, RFS, Low Frequency Reciever, LFR, Data:

The RFS is the high frequency component of the FIELDS experiment on the Parker Solar Probe spacecraft, see reference [1]. For a full description of the FIELDS experiment, see reference [2]. For a description of the RFS, see reference [3].

The RFS produces auto and cross spectral data products in two frequency ranges, the Low Frequency Reciever range and the High Frequency Receiver range. Telemetered spectral data products for both HFR and LFR contain 64 frequency bins, with the LFR typically covering a frequency range from 10.5 kHz to 1.7 MHz, and the HFR covering from 1.3 MHz to 19.2 MHz, with approximately logarithmically spaced bins. LFR high-resolution spectra contain 32 finely spaced frequency bins near the plasma frequency. The exact frequency bins are selectable and are included as metadata variables in this file.

The Level 2 data products contained in this data file have been calibrated for the preamp and RFS analog section response, the Polyphase Filter Bank, PFB, and the Fast Fourier Transform, FFT, spectral processing as described in reference [3]. Corrections for base capacitance and antenna effective length have not been applied. These corrections will be applied in Level 3 RFS data. Therefore, the units for all spectral quantities are given in V^2/Hz.

The time resolution of the RFS data vary with instrument mode. During encounter, which is when PSP is within 0.25 astronomical units, AU, of the Sun, the cadence for RFS HFR and LFR spectra is typically about 7 s. During cruise mode, which is the default mode for operations outside of 0.25 AU, the cadence for HFR and LFR spectra is about 56 s.

References:

    1. Fox, N.J., Velli, M.C., Bale, S.D., et al., Space Sci Rev (2016), 204:7, DOI:10.1007/s11214-015-0211-6
    1. Bale, S.D., Goetz, K., Harvey, P.R., et al., Space Sci Rev (2016), 204:49, DOI:10.1007/s11214-016-0244-5
    1. Pulupa, M., Bale, S.D., Bonnell, J.W., et al., JGR Space Physics (2017), 122, 2836-2854, DOI:10.1002/2016JA023345

Description

PSP/FIELDS data release 7, on April 4, 2021, includes data from PSP Encounter 6 (September 2020). All data up to and including December 2020 are now publicly available. For this data release, all DFB cross spectra have been reprocessed (with a new version number), and a subset of MAG data has also been reprocessed (with a new version number).

Over Range Flag, LFR, Auto Spectra, Averages, Ch. 0: V1-V2
Set

ParameterKey
psp_fld_l2_rfs_lfr_auto_averages_ch0_V1V2_hl
Description

Over Range Flag, Low Frequency Receiver, LFR, Auto Spectra, Averages, Channel 0: V1-V2 dipole antenna signal

Caveats
Overrange flag for XFR auto and cross reduced spectra. The flag indicates whether or not at least one out of range condition occurred in at least one input waveform collected during the LFR or HFR accumulation interval (see Ref. [3]). 0: No overrange conditions, 1: Overrange in Low Gain but not in High Gain, 2: Overrange in High Gain but not in Low Gain, 3: Overrange in Low Gain and High Gain.

PT7S

ParameterKey
psp_fld_l2_rfs_lfr_auto_averages_ch0_V2V4_hl
Description

Over Range Flag, Low Frequency Receiver, LFR, Auto Spectra, Averages, Channel 0: V2-V4 dipole antenna signal

Caveats
Overrange flag for XFR auto and cross reduced spectra. The flag indicates whether or not at least one out of range condition occurred in at least one input waveform collected during the LFR or HFR accumulation interval (see Ref. [3]). 0: No overrange conditions, 1: Overrange in Low Gain but not in High Gain, 2: Overrange in High Gain but not in Low Gain, 3: Overrange in Low Gain and High Gain.

PT7S

Description

Caveats
Overrange flag for XFR auto and cross reduced spectra. The flag indicates whether or not at least one out of range condition occurred in at least one input waveform collected during the LFR or HFR accumulation interval (see Ref. [3]). 0: No overrange conditions, 1: Overrange in Low Gain but not in High Gain, 2: Overrange in High Gain but not in Low Gain, 3: Overrange in Low Gain and High Gain.

psp_fld_l2_rfs_lfr_hires_averages_ch0_V1_hl
Description

Over Range Flag, Low Frequency Receiver, LFR, High Resolution Auto Spectra, Averages, Channel 0: V1 monopole antenna signal

Caveats
Overrange flag for XFR auto and cross reduced spectra. The flag indicates whether or not at least one out of range condition occurred in at least one input waveform collected during the LFR or HFR accumulation interval (see Ref. [3]). 0: No overrange conditions, 1: Overrange in Low Gain but not in High Gain, 2: Overrange in High Gain but not in Low Gain, 3: Overrange in Low Gain and High Gain.

Over Range Flag, Low Frequency Receiver, LFR, Cross Spectra, Imaginary Part, Channel 0: V1-V2 dipole antenna signal, Channel 1: V4 monopole antenna signal

Caveats
Overrange flag for XFR auto and cross reduced spectra. The flag indicates whether or not at least one out of range condition occurred in at least one input waveform collected during the LFR or HFR accumulation interval (see Ref. [3]). 0: No overrange conditions, 1: Overrange in Low Gain but not in High Gain, 2: Overrange in High Gain but not in Low Gain, 3: Overrange in Low Gain and High Gain.

psp_fld_l2_rfs_lfr_cross_im_V1V3_SCM_hl
Description

Over Range Flag, Low Frequency Receiver, LFR, Cross Spectra, Imaginary Part, Channel 0: V1-V3 dipole antenna signal, Channel 1: Search Coil Magnetometer, SCM, signal

Caveats
Overrange flag for XFR auto and cross reduced spectra. The flag indicates whether or not at least one out of range condition occurred in at least one input waveform collected during the LFR or HFR accumulation interval (see Ref. [3]). 0: No overrange conditions, 1: Overrange in Low Gain but not in High Gain, 2: Overrange in High Gain but not in Low Gain, 3: Overrange in Low Gain and High Gain.

Over Range Flag, Low Frequency Receiver, LFR, Cross Spectra, Imaginary Part, Channel 0: V1 monopole antenna signal, Channel 1: V3-V4 dipole antenna signal

Caveats
Overrange flag for XFR auto and cross reduced spectra. The flag indicates whether or not at least one out of range condition occurred in at least one input waveform collected during the LFR or HFR accumulation interval (see Ref. [3]). 0: No overrange conditions, 1: Overrange in Low Gain but not in High Gain, 2: Overrange in High Gain but not in Low Gain, 3: Overrange in Low Gain and High Gain.

psp_fld_l2_rfs_lfr_cross_im_GND_V3V2_hl
Description

Over Range Flag, Low Frequency Receiver, LFR, Cross Spectra, Imaginary Part, Channel 0: Ground, GND, signal, Channel 1: V3-V2 dipole antenna signal

Caveats
Overrange flag for XFR auto and cross reduced spectra. The flag indicates whether or not at least one out of range condition occurred in at least one input waveform collected during the LFR or HFR accumulation interval (see Ref. [3]). 0: No overrange conditions, 1: Overrange in Low Gain but not in High Gain, 2: Overrange in High Gain but not in Low Gain, 3: Overrange in Low Gain and High Gain.

PT7S

[3]). 0: No overrange conditions, 1: Overrange in Low Gain but not in High Gain, 2: Overrange in High Gain but not in Low Gain, 3: Overrange in Low Gain and High Gain.

psp_fld_l2_rfs_lfr_cross_re_V1V3_V3V2_hl
Description

Over Range Flag, Low Frequency Receiver, LFR, Cross Spectra, Real Part, Channel 0: V1-V3 dipole antenna signal, Channel 1: V3-V2 dipole antenna signal

Caveats
Overrange flag for XFR auto and cross reduced spectra. The flag indicates whether or not at least one out of range condition occurred in at least one input waveform collected during the LFR or HFR accumulation interval (see Ref. [3]). 0: No overrange conditions, 1: Overrange in Low Gain but not in High Gain, 2: Overrange in High Gain but not in Low Gain, 3: Overrange in Low Gain and High Gain.

psp_fld_l2_rfs_lfr_cross_re_SCM_V4_hl
Description

Over Range Flag, Low Frequency Receiver, LFR, Cross Spectra, Real Part, Channel 0: Search Coil Magnetometer, SCM, signal, Channel 1: V4 monopole antenna signal

Caveats
Overrange flag for XFR auto and cross reduced spectra. The flag indicates whether or not at least one out of range condition occurred in at least one input waveform collected during the LFR or HFR accumulation interval (see Ref. [3]). 0: No overrange conditions, 1: Overrange in Low Gain but not in High Gain, 2: Overrange in High Gain but not in Low Gain, 3: Overrange in Low Gain and High Gain.

Over Range Flag, Low Frequency Receiver, LFR, Cross Spectra, Real Part, Channel 0: Ground, GND, signal, Channel 1: Search Coil Magnetometer, SCM, signal

Caveats
Overrange flag for XFR auto and cross reduced spectra. The flag indicates whether or not at least one out of range condition occurred in at least one input waveform collected during the LFR or HFR accumulation interval (see Ref. [3]). 0: No overrange conditions, 1: Overrange in Low Gain but not in High Gain, 2: Overrange in High Gain but not in Low Gain, 3: Overrange in Low Gain and High Gain.

Parameter #996

Set
Time Series defined by using: EPOCH_LFR_COHER_V1V3_V2
ParameterKey
psp_fld_l2_rfs_lfr_coher_V1V3_V2_hl
Description

Over Range Flag, Low Frequency Receiver, LFR, Cross Spectra, Coherence, Channel 0: V1-V3 dipole antenna signal, Channel 1: V2 monopole antenna signal

Caveats
Overrange flag for XFR auto and cross reduced spectra. The flag indicates whether or not at least one out of range condition occurred in at least one input waveform collected during the LFR or HFR accumulation interval (see Ref. [3]). 0: No overrange conditions, 1: Overrange in Low Gain but not in High Gain, 2: Overrange in High Gain but not in Low Gain, 3: Overrange in Low Gain and High Gain.

psp_fld_l2_rfs_lfr_coher_SCM_V2_hl

Caveats

The flag indicates whether or not at least one out of range condition occurred in at least one input waveform collected during the LFR or HFR accumulation interval (see Ref. [3]). 0: No overrange conditions, 1: Overrange in Low Gain but not in High Gain, 2: Overrange in High Gain but not in Low Gain, 3: Overrange in Low Gain and High Gain.

psp_fld_l2_rfs_lfr_coher_V1_V1V4_hl
Description

Over Range Flag, Low Frequency Receiver, LFR, Cross Spectra, Coherence, Channel 0: V1 monopole antenna signal, Channel 1: V1-V4 dipole antenna signal

Caveats
Overrange flag for XFR auto and cross reduced spectra. The flag indicates whether or not at least one out of range condition occurred in at least one input waveform collected during the LFR or HFR accumulation interval (see Ref. [3]). 0: No overrange conditions, 1: Overrange in Low Gain but not in High Gain, 2: Overrange in High Gain but not in Low Gain, 3: Overrange in Low Gain and High Gain.

Over Range Flag, LFR, Cross Spectra, Coherence, Ch. 0: V3, Ch. 1: V2
Set
Time Series defined by using: EPOCH_LFR_COHER_V3_V2
ParameterKey
psp_fld_l2_rfs_lfr_coher_V3_V2_hl
Description

Over Range Flag, Low Frequency Receiver, LFR, Cross Spectra, Coherence, Channel 0: V3 monopole antenna signal, Channel 1: V2 monopole antenna signal

Caveats
Overrange flag for XFR auto and cross reduced spectra. The flag indicates whether or not at least one out of range condition occurred in at least one input waveform collected during the LFR or HFR accumulation interval (see Ref. [3]). 0: No overrange conditions, 1: Overrange in Low Gain but not in High Gain, 2: Overrange in High Gain but not in Low Gain, 3: Overrange in Low Gain and High Gain.
Cadence
PT7S
RenderingHints
DisplayType
TimeSeries
AxisLabel
LFR coher V3_V2 hl
ValueFormat
I6
ScaleType
LinearScale
ValidMin
0
ValidMax
3

-32768

psp_fld_l2_rfs_lfr_phase_V1V2_V3V4_hl
Description

Over Range Flag, Low Frequency Receiver, LFR, Cross Spectra, Phase, Channel 0: V1-V2 dipole antenna signal, Channel 1: V3-V4 dipole antenna signal

Caveats
Overrange flag for XFR auto and cross reduced spectra. The flag indicates whether or not at least one out of range condition occurred in at least one input waveform collected during the LFR or HFR accumulation interval (see Ref. [3]). 0: No overrange conditions, 1: Overrange in Low Gain but not in High Gain, 2: Overrange in High Gain but not in Low Gain, 3: Overrange in Low Gain and High Gain.

Set

ParameterKey
psp_fld_l2_rfs_lfr_phase_V2V4_V3V4_hl
Description

Over Range Flag, Low Frequency Receiver, LFR, Cross Spectra, Phase, Channel 0: V2-V4 dipole antenna signal, Channel 1: V3-V4 dipole antenna signal

Caveats
Overrange flag for XFR auto and cross reduced spectra. The flag indicates whether or not at least one out of range condition occurred in at least one input waveform collected during the LFR or HFR accumulation interval (see Ref. [3]). 0: No overrange conditions, 1: Overrange in Low Gain but not in High Gain, 2: Overrange in High Gain but not in Low Gain, 3: Overrange in Low Gain and High Gain.

Over Range Flag, Low Frequency Receiver, LFR, Cross Spectra, Phase, Channel 0: V3 monopole antenna signal, Channel 1: Search Coil Magnetometer, SCM, signal

Caveats
Overrange flag for XFR auto and cross reduced spectra. The flag indicates whether or not at least one out of range condition occurred in at least one input waveform collected during the LFR or HFR accumulation interval (see Ref. [3]). 0: No overrange conditions, 1: Overrange in Low Gain but not in High Gain, 2: Overrange in High Gain but not in Low Gain, 3: Overrange in Low Gain and High Gain.
Cadence
PT7S

Parameter #1512
Name
Over Range Flag, LFR, Cross Spectra, Phase, Ch. 0: GND, Ch. 1: GND
Set
Time Series defined by using: EPOCH_LFR_PHASE_GND_GND
ParameterKey
psp_fld_l2_rfs_lfr_phase_GND_GND_hl
Description

Over Range Flag, Low Frequency Receiver, LFR, Cross Spectra, Phase, Channel 0: Ground, GND, signal, Channel 1: Ground, GND, signal

Caveats
Overrange flag for XFR auto and cross reduced spectra. The flag indicates whether or not at least one out of range condition occurred in at least one input waveform collected during the LFR or HFR accumulation interval (see Ref. [3]). 0: No overrange conditions, 1: Overrange in Low Gain but not in High Gain, 2: Overrange in High Gain but not in Low Gain, 3: Overrange in Low Gain and High Gain.
Cadence
PT7S

TimeSeries

Parameter #1522
Name
FIELDS Data Quality Flags
Set
Time Series defined by using: EPOCH_QUALITY_FLAGS
ParameterKey
psp_fld_l2_quality_flags
Description

FIELDS Instrument Suite Data Quality Flags

Caveats
FIELDS quality flags: These flags are bitwise variables, meaning that multiple flags can be set simultaneously for a single time by adding flag values. Current flagged values are: * 1: FIELDS Antenna Bias Sweep * 2: PSP Thruster Firing * 4: SCM Calibration * 8: PSP Rotations for MAG Calibration, MAG Rolls * 16: FIELDS MAG Calibration Sequence * 32: SWEAP SPC in Electron Mode * 64: PSP Solar Limb Sensor, SLS, Test * 128: PSP Spacecraft is off Umbra Pointing, Heat Shield not pointed Sunward * 256: High Frequency Noise affecting RFS and TDS Receivers * 512: Antennas driven towards the FIELDS Power Supply Rails A value of zero corresponds to no set flags. Not all flags are relevant to all FIELDS data products, refer to notes in the CDF metadata and on the FIELDS Satellite Operations Center, SOC, website for information on how the various flags impact FIELDS data. For more information on the quality flags describing high frequency noise and antennas driven to the rails, see release notes for PSP/FIELDS releases 8 and 9. Additional flagged items may be added in the future.
Cadence
PT7S
RenderingHints
AxisLabel
flag
ValueFormat
I10
ValidMin
0
ValidMax
1023
FillValue
4294967295
Support
Qualifier
Scalar
SupportQuantity
InstrumentMode
